# Global Styles First

Before editing styles in two or more files, stop and check whether one change in the global stylesheet can achieve the same outcome.

## When this applies

- The same visual change is needed in multiple sections, pages, or components
- Typography, color, spacing, or layout tweaks that feel site-wide
- You are about to repeat the same override in `about.scss`, `services.scss`, `contact.scss`, or other page SCSS files

## What to check first (in order)

1. **`src/assets/sass/root.scss`** — CSS variables in `:root`, dark mode tokens, `.cs-*` utilities, nav, footer, and other shared section patterns
2. **Existing shared classes** — `.cs-title`, `.cs-topper`, `.cs-text`, `.cs-button-solid`, etc.
3. **`src/assets/sass/local.scss`** — only if the change is page-specific, not site-wide
4. **`src/assets/sass/critical.scss`** — only for above-the-fold overrides that cannot live in `root.scss`

The comment at the top of `root.scss` states the intent: site-wide edits belong there so changes apply everywhere from one place.

## Decision rule

| Situation | Approach |
|-----------|----------|
| Change applies everywhere or to a shared `.cs-*` pattern | Edit `root.scss` once |
| Change affects one page only | Edit that page's SCSS (e.g. `about.scss`) |
| Unsure | Default to `root.scss` first; narrow scope only if global causes unwanted side effects |

## Examples

```scss
// ❌ BAD — same title color in about.scss, services.scss, contact.scss
#about-hero .cs-title,
#services-hero .cs-title { color: var(--primary); }

// ✅ GOOD — update once in root.scss if all titles should change
.cs-title { color: var(--headerColor); }
// Or update --headerColor / --primary in :root for a brand-wide shift
```

```scss
// ❌ BAD — duplicate section padding across multiple page files
#about-services { padding: 5rem 1rem; }
#contact-info { padding: 5rem 1rem; }

// ✅ GOOD — use or update --sectionPadding in :root
section { padding: var(--sectionPadding); }
```

If a global change would affect unrelated areas, add or extend a shared class in `root.scss` rather than copying overrides into multiple page SCSS files.
